## LTTB (Largest-Triangle-Three-Buckets) Downsampling

Critical algorithm for handling massive time series data. Preserves visual shape
while dramatically reducing point count.

### Why LTTB?

| Method | Visual Fidelity | Performance | Use Case |
|--------|----------------|-------------|----------|
| **Raw Data** | Perfect | Slow | Small datasets |
| **Skip Sampling** | Poor (loses peaks) | Fast | Never recommended |
| **Averaging** | Medium (smooths) | Fast | Statistical analysis |
